---

## Architecture Decisions (Read Before Touching Code)

### Music Source: YouTube IFrame API (NOT Data API)
- **Data API** (search.list): 10,000 quota units/day, 100 units per search = only ~100 searches/day free. **AVOID for playback.**
- **IFrame API**: Zero quota. Unlimited playback. **Use for audio.**
- **Strategy:** YouTube Data API for search ONLY (server-side proxied + cached). YouTube IFrame for actual playback.

### No Backend Server
- **No NestJS. No Express. No Prisma.**
- All "backend" logic lives in **Vercel Edge Functions** (`/api/*.ts`) co-located in the same repo.
- Database + Auth: **Supabase** (PostgreSQL, Row Level Security, built-in JWT auth).
- Caching: **Upstash Redis** (free tier) for cross-user YouTube search cache (24hr TTL).

### State: Zustand Only
- No React Context for global state (audio, queue, user, theme).
- Context ONLY for local component trees if strictly necessary (e.g., DragContext for queue reordering).

### Data Fetching: TanStack Query
- Wraps all service calls. Aggressive stale-while-revalidate.
- Prevents redundant YouTube API hits at the client layer.

---

## Tech Stack (Locked)

| Layer | Choice | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Framework | React 18 + Vite | Fast HMR, Capacitor-compatible |
| Language | 100% TypeScript (.ts/.tsx) | Type safety, no .js/.jsx |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v3 + CSS Variables | Dynamic theming via CSS vars |
| Animations | Framer Motion + GSAP | Page transitions + vinyl/panda micro-animations |
| State | Zustand | No context boilerplate, devtools, immutable updates |
| Server State | TanStack Query v5 | Caching, background refetch, deduplication |
| Auth/DB | Supabase | Postgres, RLS, JWT, realtime |
| API Cache | Upstash Redis | Cross-user YouTube search result cache |
| Audio | Howler.js | Background play, mobile compatibility, Capacitor-safe |
| PWA | vite-plugin-pwa | Service worker, manifest, offline shell |
| Router | React Router v6 | Nested routes, lazy loading |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod | Type-safe validation |
| Color Extraction | node-vibrant (browser build) | Album art в†’ theme colors |

